Because Spring Boot will automatically add embedded Tomcat dependencies as default choice while you add `spring-boot-starter-web` into your pom file. And you can directly run you application as a standalone web application.  

As I said in the comment under your question, you need to exclude the dependency of `spring-boot-starter-tomcat` in `spring-boot-starter-web` if you want to deploy your WAR file to any Servlet 3 container. 

Foe example:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-web&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;exclusions&gt;
            &lt;exclusion&gt;
               &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
               &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-tomcat&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;/exclusion&gt;
        &lt;/exclusions&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

i think there is a misunderstanding here, in spring boot we don&#39;t need to create a war in order to deploy in tomcat server. The advantage of using spring boot is that it adds all the required dependencies. So you need to just develop the application

Here are the following steps you can try to make it work.
1) if you want your project to create a war file and deploy it in an external server you need to set your scope of the tomcat dependency in spring boot to &quot;provided&quot;.

        `&lt;dependency&gt;
			&lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
			&lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-tomcat&lt;/artifactId&gt;
			&lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;
		&lt;/dependency&gt;`
 

2) if you want your application to be deployed automatically after ruuning the spring boot application you set the scope to &quot;compile&quot;.

        `&lt;dependency&gt;
			&lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
			&lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-tomcat&lt;/artifactId&gt;
		&lt;/dependency&gt;`

remove scope :

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-test&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;
    
or replace with compile:
    
    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-test&lt;/artifactId&gt;
       	&lt;scope&gt;compile&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

**Adding this Resolved my problem**


    &lt;dependency&gt;
    	&lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
    	&lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-tomcat&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    	&lt;version&gt;2.4.5&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

I solve this by :

1 Edit pom.xml change scope provider -&gt; compile  

    &lt;dependency&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-tomcat&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;scope&gt;provider&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

2 Right Click Project -&gt; Maven -&gt; Reload Project

3 Run Application

